wikipedia_page.main: Tim Whitehead (Born 12 December 1950 in Liverpool) is a British jazz musician (soprano, alto and tenor saxophone, flute).

response: Through the 1990s, Jacobsen worked with Tim Whitehead's quartet and trio; he played on two of Whitehead's albums--Authentic (1991), and Silence Between Waves (1994). It was Whitehead who noted that Jacobsen spent much of his time in the East End of London, playing with with unknown and/or struggling musicians and, as a result, never got the press attention he deserved.
